<chapter>
  <title><xi:include href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_Listed_Option"
  xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" /> Module</title>

  <para role="TEXT">The <xi:include href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_Listed_Option"
  xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" /> module enables you, on behalf
  of your company, to arrange listed option trades.</para>

  <para role="TEXT">For basic features common to all modules, such as basic terminology
  and the use of lists and forms, see chapter
  <emphasis>Introduction</emphasis>. For descriptions of functions, see
  chapter <emphasis>Functions</emphasis>.</para>

  <para role="TEXT">This chapter gives detailed descriptions of the input forms used by
  this module, and describes any features specific to this module.</para>

  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>Listed Option Trades</title>

    <para role="TEXT">A listed option (also called an exchange-traded option) is an option
    that is sold on a registered exchange, such as the Chicago Board Options
    Exchange (CBOE) or Euronext. Listed options cover securities such as
    common stocks, ETFs, market indexes and commodities. All listed options
    have stated exercise prices and expiration dates.</para>
  </section>

